==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: lipophobic
<hw>lipophobic</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Not soluble
in lipids, or in non-polar solvents; -- of chemical substances or parts
of molecules; <as>as, the <ex>lipophobic</ex> end of a detergent is
solvated in water</as>. Contrasted to <contr>lipophilic</contr> or
<contr>nonpolar</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lipothymic</ent>⟦br⟧
